The paper deals with the problem of reliable information transmission over permutation channels, which are relevant to packet networks. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new type of code called multiset codes, which is a generalization of subset codes. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a coding-theoretic framework that is similar to one proposed for operator channels, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CC) sub-category.
